04:50.159 --> 04:53.031
-SO, ONCE I GOT MY TIMING DOWN,
MY DIVES WERE UNBELIEVABLE.

04:53.162 --> 04:54.816
-YEAH?
-YEAH.

04:54.946 --> 04:57.427
IT'S LIKE I HAD TOTAL COMMAND
OF MY BODY, YOU KNOW?

04:57.558 --> 04:59.516
IT'S LIKE THIS FEELING OF...

04:59.647 --> 05:02.389
-POWER.
-YEAH, EXACTLY.

05:02.519 --> 05:05.392
-WELL, YOU'VE COME A LONG WAY
FROM YOUR ROOKIE SCHOOL
PIER JUMP, I'D SAY.

05:05.522 --> 05:08.351
-OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE THAT.
I WAS SO WIGGED.

05:08.482 --> 05:10.353
I COULDN'T EVEN MOVE,
LET ALONE JUMP.

05:10.484 --> 05:13.965
[SIGHS]
OH, I DON'T EVER WANT
TO HAVE THAT FEELING AGAIN.

05:14.096 --> 05:15.663
THAT'S WHY DIVING
IS SO IMPORTANT TO ME.

05:15.793 --> 05:18.405
BECAUSE I DID IT, YOU KNOW?
I CONQUERED MY FEAR.

05:18.535 --> 05:20.145
-GOOD FOR YOU, HONEY.

05:20.276 --> 05:22.104
-[PHONE RINGS]
-OH, I'LL GET THAT.

05:22.234 --> 05:23.279
-OKAY.

05:30.591 --> 05:32.723
-MOM, THERE'S AN EMERGENCY.
I'VE GOT TO GO.

05:32.854 --> 05:35.247
-[POLICE SPEAKING]
-[SIREN BLARING]

05:44.431 --> 05:45.823
-ALL RIGHT.
EVERYBODY'S HERE, HUH?

05:45.954 --> 05:47.782
-IS IT THE KID WHO FELL
IN THE STORM DRAIN?

05:47.912 --> 05:49.958
-YEAH, YEAH.
IF WE HAD GOTTEN TO IT
A LITTLE EARLIER,

05:50.088 --> 05:51.481
MAYBE WE WOULDN'T
BE HERE RIGHT NOW.

05:51.612 --> 05:53.178
LET ME MAKE SURE
WE'VE GOT THE RIGHT GEAR.

05:53.309 --> 05:54.310
-GOT IT.

05:57.879 --> 05:59.271
-IS THIS ABOUT
WHERE HE ENDED UP?

05:59.402 --> 06:01.099
-YEAH, WE THINK HE'S
SOMEWHERE IN THIS AREA.

06:05.539 --> 06:07.410
-DO YOU THINK THAT'S
THE BOY'S PARENTS?

06:08.411 --> 06:09.804
-YEAH, LOOKS LIKE IT.

06:11.414 --> 06:13.547
-IT MUST BE SO HORRIBLE
JUST STANDING AROUND,

06:13.677 --> 06:16.376
WAITING FOR THEM
TO RECOVER YOUR KID'S BODY.

06:19.030 --> 06:20.641
HOW OLD WAS HE?

06:20.771 --> 06:21.816
-12.

06:24.862 --> 06:26.995
-THANKS.

06:27.125 --> 06:28.518
-I THOUGHT YOU HAD
AN IMPORTANT DINNER
WITH YOUR PARENTS TONIGHT.

06:28.649 --> 06:30.564
-OH, HOBIE WILL LET THEM IN.

06:30.694 --> 06:32.392
TO TELL YOU THE TRUTH,
I'M NOT THAT ANXIOUS
TO GET THERE.

06:32.522 --> 06:34.524
-WHAT'S IT ABOUT?
-I DON'T KNOW.

06:34.655 --> 06:36.787
MOM SAID SHE HAD SOMETHING
IMPORTANT TO TELL ME.

06:36.918 --> 06:39.442
-MAYBE IT'S GOOD NEWS.
-I DON'T KNOW.

06:44.969 --> 06:47.276
-I'VE NEVER SEEN
A DEAD BODY BEFORE.

06:47.407 --> 06:49.974
-I JUST DON'T WANT TO HAVE
TO LOOK AT HIS FACE.

06:50.105 --> 06:52.499
-WELL, HOPEFULLY, WE WON'T
BE THE ONES WHO FIND HIM.

06:54.414 --> 06:56.328
-HOW'S YOUR DIVING COMING?

06:56.459 --> 06:59.593
-PRETTY GOOD.
I HIT A DOUBLE-TWISTING,
ONE AND A HALF TODAY.

06:59.723 --> 07:02.857
-GREAT. READY FOR A LITTLE
SYNCHRONIZED SWIMMING?

07:02.987 --> 07:04.859
OKAY, EVERYBODY, LISTEN UP.

07:04.989 --> 07:07.992
THE BODY IS TRAPPED SOMEWHERE
BETWEEN HERE AND THE BRIDGE.

07:08.123 --> 07:10.908
WE SWIM, DIVE, AND SURFACE
IN UNISON.

07:11.039 --> 07:13.215
NEWMIE AND I WILL
TAKE THE CENTER.

07:13.345 --> 07:15.304
EVERYBODY ELSE, SPREAD OUT.
KEEP AN EYE ON THE LIFEGUARD
NEXT TO YOU.

07:15.435 --> 07:16.436
BEACONS ON.

07:18.525 --> 07:19.526
STICKS.

07:23.617 --> 07:25.749
OKAY. LET'S DO IT.

07:37.152 --> 07:38.806
-LOOKS GOOD. I'M ROLLING.

07:43.811 --> 07:46.683
-MITCH: ONE, TWO, THREE!

08:20.369 --> 08:24.678
ON THREE, READY.
ONE... TWO... THREE!

08:57.711 --> 09:01.541
ONE... TWO... THREE!

10:26.538 --> 10:29.193
THEY WANT TO INTERVIEW YOU
FOR THE 11:00 NEWS.

10:29.324 --> 10:33.067
IT'S UP TO YOU.
I'LL TELL THEM "NO" IF YOU WANT.
-YEAH, AND WHILE YOU'RE AT IT,

10:33.197 --> 10:35.330
WHY DON'T YOU TELL THEM
TO LEAVE THOSE
POOR PEOPLE ALONE?

10:35.460 --> 10:36.853
THEIR KID JUST DIED.

10:39.116 --> 10:41.423
-TRY AND THINK ABOUT
ALL THE LIVES YOU SAVED, HUH?

10:43.425 --> 10:44.295
YOU ALL RIGHT?

10:45.514 --> 10:46.776
-I'LL BE OKAY.

10:47.603 --> 10:50.388
I'M MORE WORRIED ABOUT SUMMER.
HAVE YOU SEEN HER?

10:50.519 --> 10:53.957
-NO, NO, BUT I'M SURE
SHE'S AROUND HERE SOMEPLACE.

11:14.891 --> 11:16.806
-CHEERLEADER.
YOU'RE A CHEERLEADER!

11:17.589 --> 11:19.896
UH, NO. NO. A BIRD.

11:20.027 --> 11:22.246
SOME KIND OF A BIRD, RIGHT?

11:22.986 --> 11:24.814
-WHERE'S YOUR FATHER?
HE WAS SUPPOSED TO BE HERE
AN HOUR AGO.

11:24.945 --> 11:27.948
-OH, AL, HE CAN'T ANSWER THAT
UNTIL WE GUESS WHAT HE IS!

11:29.950 --> 11:30.951
-HE'S A FLAMINGO.

11:32.909 --> 11:36.217
-UH, YOU! YOU. BOY? BOY.

11:38.001 --> 11:38.915
KID.

11:40.917 --> 11:44.181
"FLAMINGO KID"!
-YEAH, ALL RIGHT! WE GOT IT!

11:45.008 --> 11:46.357
-WHY DON'T YOU
GO HUG YOUR GRANDDAD?

11:46.488 --> 11:48.142
HE'S THE ONE
THAT GOT THE HARD PART.

11:49.230 --> 11:51.362
-ALL RIGHT, NOW TELL ME,
WHAT IS "THE FLAMINGO KID"?

11:51.493 --> 11:54.104
-IT WAS A MOVIE.
-WITH MATT DILLON.

11:54.235 --> 11:55.323
-THE MARSHAL ON "GUNSMOKE"?

11:56.193 --> 11:58.848
-WHAT WAS "GUNSMOKE"?
-IT WAS A TV SHOW.

11:58.979 --> 11:59.806
-WHAT WAS IT ABOUT?

12:01.155 --> 12:02.809
-WHAT WAS WHAT ABOUT?
-HOBIE: "GUNSMOKE."

12:02.939 --> 12:04.462
-HI, MOM.
-HI, DEAR.

12:04.593 --> 12:06.073
IT WAS A WESTERN,
WHERE, IF SOMEBODY TOLD YOU

12:06.203 --> 12:07.509
THEY WERE GOING TO MEET YOU
AT HIGH NOON,

12:07.639 --> 12:09.467
THEY'D WERE THERE AT HIGH NOON.

12:09.598 --> 12:13.036
-SORRY I'M LATE.
WE HAD AN EMERGENCY.
DINNER SMELLS GREAT.

12:13.167 --> 12:15.386
-AND IF A COWBOY
WAS LATE FOR DINNER,

12:15.517 --> 12:17.475
HIS MEAT WOULD BE
AS TOUGH AS BEEF JERKY.

12:17.606 --> 12:22.176
-HE'S MADE HIS POINT, HASN'T HE?
-I LOVE BEEF JERKY.

12:24.178 --> 12:25.048
-MOM?

12:27.355 --> 12:28.225
MOM, YOU HOME?

12:57.080 --> 12:58.908
-MORE COFFEE?
-YEAH, WHY NOT?

12:59.387 --> 13:01.868
-SURE GLAD YOU'RE HERE, GRANDMA.
IT'S NICE TO HAVE SOMEBODY
HELPING ME...

13:01.998 --> 13:04.566
-SO, UH...

13:04.696 --> 13:08.135
MOM SAID THERE'S SOMETHING
YOU WANT TO TALK TO ME ABOUT.
OH, YOU WANT TO WAIT FOR MOM?

13:08.265 --> 13:11.965
-NO, NO. WHAT THE HELL.
I'VE DECIDED TO RETIRE.

13:12.095 --> 13:15.707
-GREAT, DAD! THAT'S GREAT!
YOU DESERVE TO ENJOY
THE REST OF YOUR LIFE.

13:15.838 --> 13:17.361
-IF PEOPLE GOT
WHAT THEY DESERVED,

13:17.492 --> 13:18.928
THERE'D BE JUSTICE
IN THIS WORLD.

13:19.581 --> 13:23.063
I BUILT MY FIRM
FROM A ONE-MAN OPERATION
TO 150 EMPLOYEES,

13:23.193 --> 13:25.413
FROM DESIGNING BUS STOPS
TO SKYSCRAPERS.

13:25.543 --> 13:26.893
-YOU'RE A GREAT ARCHITECT.

13:27.023 --> 13:29.243
-AND SO WERE YOU.
-NO, I WASN'T.

13:29.373 --> 13:31.071
-YES, YOU WERE!

13:31.201 --> 13:32.681
AND YOU HAD THE POTENTIAL
TO BE EVEN BETTER THAN I AM.

13:32.812 --> 13:35.205
-DAD, YOU ALWAYS LOVED
ARCHITECTURAL DESIGN,

13:35.336 --> 13:36.728
AND BELIEVE ME,
I ALWAYS HATED IT.

13:38.078 --> 13:39.601
-OH, BUT YOU LOVE RUNNING
AROUND THE BEACH ALL DAY,

13:39.731 --> 13:42.604
PUTTING DESIGNS ON PRETTY GIRLS,
AND DEEPENING YOUR TAN.

13:42.734 --> 13:45.259
-IF YOU STILL THINK THAT
THAT'S ALL MY JOB ENTAILS,

13:45.389 --> 13:48.305
THEN FINE,
YES, I DO LOVE IT.

13:48.436 --> 13:51.004
-MITCH, YOU'RE NOT
A TEENAGER ANYMORE.

13:51.134 --> 13:54.355
YOU'RE A 37-YEAR-OLD MAN.
IT'S TIME FOR YOU TO CONSIDER
YOUR FUTURE IN THE LONG-TERM.

13:54.485 --> 13:57.053
HOBIE'S FUTURE!
-MY WHAT?

13:57.184 --> 13:58.315
-YOUR FUTURE.

13:59.403 --> 14:01.405
LET'S GO IN THE DEN, HUH?
-YEAH, OKAY.

14:04.582 --> 14:08.064
-HEY, DAD,
WHAT ABOUT MY FUTURE?

14:08.195 --> 14:11.546
-ASK YOUR GRANDMA.
SHE READS TAROT CARDS.

14:11.676 --> 14:13.896
-WELL, COME ON! I KNOW
THAT THERE'S A DECK UPSTAIRS.

14:14.027 --> 14:18.945
-WHOA! LET US ASCEND,
AND I WILL REVEAL TO YOU
THE MYSTERIES OF THE UNIVERSE.

14:22.035 --> 14:24.124
-OKAY, LET'S CUT THROUGH IT.

14:24.254 --> 14:26.126
YOU WANT TO RETIRE
BECAUSE YOU WANT ME
TO TAKE OVER THE BUSINESS.

14:26.256 --> 14:27.431
IS THAT IT?

14:28.432 --> 14:31.044
-YOU MAKE IT SOUND
LIKE I'M TRYING TO SHOVE
GARBAGE IN YOUR FACE.

14:31.174 --> 14:33.916
I'M OFFERING YOU
A LIFETIME OF WORK
ON A SILVER PLATTER, MITCH!

14:34.047 --> 14:36.310
-DAD, YOUR LIFE, YOUR WORK...

14:36.440 --> 14:37.833
I'VE GOT A LIFE.
I'VE GOT A CAREER.

14:37.964 --> 14:40.662
NO, YOU HAVE A JOB,
NOT A CAREER.

14:40.792 --> 14:43.578
-I'M OFFERING YOU
THE BATON, MITCH.
GRAB IT! RUN WITH IT!

14:43.708 --> 14:48.452
-I DID THAT ALREADY, REMEMBER?
I GOT MY ARCHITECTURAL DEGREE
FOR YOU! I WORKED AT THE FIRM.

14:48.583 --> 14:51.542
AFTER TWO MONTHS,
WE WERE MISERABLE
WITH EACH OTHER.

14:51.673 --> 14:54.632
-WELL, THIS TIME,
I WON'T BE AROUND SO MUCH,
TO MAKE YOU SO MISERABLE.

14:54.763 --> 14:58.245
-OH, COME ON, DAD. I...

14:58.375 --> 15:01.074
I APPRECIATE THE OFFER.
I REALLY DO,

15:01.204 --> 15:03.032
BUT HOBIE AND I ARE HAPPY
HERE IN LOS ANGELES.

15:03.163 --> 15:05.252
WE DON'T WANT TO JUST PICK UP
AND MOVE TO PHOENIX.

15:05.382 --> 15:08.690
-BECAUSE THERE'S NO OCEAN?
-BECAUSE THERE'S NO REASON.

15:08.820 --> 15:12.085
-FINE. YOU'RE RIGHT.
IT'S MY LIFE. WHO AM I
TO IMPOSE IT ON YOU?

15:12.737 --> 15:14.914
-DAD--
-AH... IRENE!

15:15.044 --> 15:16.741
IT'S TIME. LET'S GO!

15:16.872 --> 15:18.308
IRENE!

16:04.572 --> 16:07.270
-MOMMY!
-SUMMER?

16:07.401 --> 16:11.361
SUMMER, HONEY, WAKE UP.
SUMMER! HONEY! WAKE UP!

16:11.492 --> 16:14.321
OH, BABY! IT'S ALL RIGHT, HONEY.
YOU WERE HAVING A DREAM.

16:14.451 --> 16:17.106
-NO, MOM, IT WASN'T A DREAM.
-YES, HONEY, IT WAS A DREAM.

16:18.673 --> 16:20.936
-REMEMBER THE EMERGENCY RESCUE
I WENT ON TONIGHT?

16:21.067 --> 16:22.329
-YES.

16:22.459 --> 16:24.940
-A LITTLE BOY DROWNED.
HE WAS ONLY 12.

16:25.071 --> 16:26.463
-OH.
-BUT, SEE...

16:27.160 --> 16:29.814
WE WERE DOING A BODY SEARCH,
AND I TOTALLY FREAKED OUT.

16:30.424 --> 16:34.341
-OH, BABY. OH, NO WONDER
YOU HAD A NIGHTMARE.

16:34.471 --> 16:37.083
-MOM, SEE, THE THING IS,
I DIDN'T FIND THE BODY.

16:37.213 --> 16:39.520
AS SOON AS I WENT UNDER WATER,
I FREAKED OUT.

16:39.650 --> 16:42.610
-HONEY, YOU WERE AFRAID
THAT YOU WOULD FIND THE BODY.

16:42.740 --> 16:44.133
NOW, THAT'S UNDERSTANDABLE.

16:44.264 --> 16:46.266
-I JUST DON'T KNOW THOUGH.

16:46.396 --> 16:49.051
I MEAN, I REALLY FEEL LIKE
IT'S SOMETHING MORE THAN THAT.

16:49.878 --> 16:53.012
-NO, HONEY. NO, IT'S OKAY.

16:54.187 --> 16:57.103
IT'S OKAY. OH.

17:33.965 --> 17:36.403
-I KNOW WHY
YOU LOVE THIS SO MUCH.

17:37.665 --> 17:40.146
-WHY CAN'T DAD UNDERSTAND IT?
-WE LIVED ON THE BEACH

17:40.276 --> 17:42.670
THE ENTIRE TIME
WHEN YOU WERE GROWING UP.

17:42.800 --> 17:47.327
IT WAS SOMEPLACE THAT HE VISITED
WHEN HE WASN'T WORKING.

17:48.415 --> 17:50.634
YEAH, HE NEVER LOVED IT
LIKE YOU DO.

17:51.940 --> 17:54.595
-YEAH, WELL, SOMETIMES,
I THINK HE NEVER LOVED ME.

17:54.725 --> 17:57.902
-DON'T YOU DARE TALK
ABOUT YOUR FATHER THAT WAY.

17:58.033 --> 18:01.689
HE LOVES YOU DEEPLY.
I GUESS IT'S HARD
FOR HIM TO SHOW IT

18:01.819 --> 18:04.083
AS IT IS FOR YOU
TO RECOGNIZE IT
WHEN HE DOES.

18:06.520 --> 18:08.783
-I KNOW. I RECOGNIZE IT.
I'M SORRY, MOM.

18:08.913 --> 18:10.480
IT'S JUST THAT...

18:11.264 --> 18:13.179
I MEAN, I KNOW HE LOVES ME.

18:14.789 --> 18:18.314
WHY DOES HE WANT ME
TO TAKE OVER A BUSINESS
THAT'S NOT GONNA MAKE ME HAPPY?

18:19.968 --> 18:21.100
-BECAUSE...

18:23.319 --> 18:25.756
IT'S THE ONLY THING
HE HAS TO LEAVE YOU.

18:31.588 --> 18:34.417
-WHAT? MOM...

18:35.549 --> 18:39.074
WHAT ARE YOU TELLING ME?
-HE HAS LYMPHOMA, MITCH.

18:40.945 --> 18:42.730
-WELL, THAT'S TREATABLE,
ISN'T IT?

18:42.860 --> 18:47.604
-THEY'VE TRIED, BUT...
IT'S GONE BEYOND THAT NOW.

18:50.259 --> 18:52.261
-HOW LONG HAVE YOU KNOWN, MOM?

18:53.784 --> 18:58.224
-A LITTLE OVER A YEAR.
-OVER A YEAR?
AND YOU DIDN'T TELL ME?

18:58.963 --> 19:02.576
-YOU KNOW YOUR FATHER.
HE WAS SO SURE HE WOULD BEAT IT.

19:03.490 --> 19:06.754
HE STARTED WORKING
ON THAT DESIGN
FOR THE UNIVERSITY COMPLEX

19:06.884 --> 19:08.408
THAT HE WAS ALWAYS
GOING ON ABOUT.

19:09.452 --> 19:11.498
HE WANTS THAT
TO BE HIS LEGACY.

19:12.673 --> 19:14.588
OF COURSE,
NOW HE REALIZES THAT...

19:14.892 --> 19:16.024
THAT HE CAN'T COMPLETE IT.

19:17.982 --> 19:21.421
THAT'S WHY HE WANTS YOU
TO FOLLOW IN HIS FOOTSTEPS,

19:21.856 --> 19:24.467
SO YOU CAN PICK UP
WHERE HE LEAVES OFF.

19:26.730 --> 19:28.297
-WHY DIDN'T HE TELL ME HIMSELF?

19:29.385 --> 19:33.302
-BECAUSE HE WANTS YOU
TO DO IT OUT OF LOVE,
NOT OBLIGATION.

19:33.433 --> 19:36.436
-OH, GEEZ. MOM...

19:38.046 --> 19:39.221
I'M SORRY.

19:46.489 --> 19:51.190
-GIRL: HERE YOU GO! GET IT!
-GIRL #2: CAUGHT IT! ALL RIGHT!

20:03.114 --> 20:04.768
-MAN: MAN, I FORGOT MY RADIO.

20:19.130 --> 20:21.437
-THAT FLOTATION DEVICE
IS VERY DANGEROUS!

20:21.568 --> 20:23.439
PLEASE BRING IT
OUT OF THE WATER!

20:32.405 --> 20:33.188
-SUMMER!

21:54.138 --> 21:55.749
YOU ALL RIGHT?

21:59.274 --> 22:02.625
SIT DOWN.
LISTEN TO ME.

22:03.452 --> 22:06.542
THIS IS WHY INFLATABLES AREN'T
ALLOWED IN THE OCEAN, OKAY?
-OKAY.

22:06.673 --> 22:08.501
-I WANT YOU TO BRING IT OVER
TO YOUR TOWEL--
-YEAH.

22:08.631 --> 22:10.241
-AND LET ALL THE AIR OUT OF IT.
-ALL RIGHT.

22:10.372 --> 22:11.330
-ALL RIGHT?
-YEAH.

22:11.460 --> 22:12.635
-ALL RIGHT.
-THANKS.

22:27.433 --> 22:28.738
-COME IN, SUMMER.

22:30.131 --> 22:32.351
WHAT'S GOING ON WITH YOU?
-NOTHING.

22:32.481 --> 22:34.744
I WAS GONNA WAVE HIM IN,
AND THEN YOU JUST RAN OUT THERE.

22:34.875 --> 22:38.661
-NO. NO, YOU WERE FREAKED,
JUST LIKE LAST NIGHT.

22:39.227 --> 22:40.446
WHAT ARE YOU SO SCARED OF?

22:41.621 --> 22:43.100
-I'M NOT SCARED OF ANYTHING.

22:44.406 --> 22:47.670
LOOK, MATT, ARE YOU STILL GOING
KAMIKAZE BIKING AFTER WORK?

22:47.801 --> 22:49.846
-YEAH. YOU WANT
TO COME AND WATCH?

22:49.977 --> 22:51.718
-SHOULD I BRING MY POM-POMS?

22:52.545 --> 22:54.285
NO, MATT, I WANT TO DO IT.

22:54.895 --> 22:56.810
-YOU WANT TO BIKE STRAIGHT
DOWN THE SIDE OF A MOUNTAIN?

22:57.463 --> 22:59.900
-I TOLD YOU, I'M NOT AFRAID.
I'LL PROVE IT.

23:00.030 --> 23:04.600
-LOOK, RELAX. COME ON.
YOU DON'T NEED TO PROVE
ANYTHING TO ME.

23:05.471 --> 23:08.082
-I KNOW WHAT I NEED,
AND I KNOW WHAT I WANT,

23:08.212 --> 23:10.040
AND I WANT TO GO
KAMIKAZE BIKING.

23:10.867 --> 23:12.652
I'LL MEET YOU OUT FRONT
OF THE HEADQUARTERS.

