26:06.347 --> 26:08.479
-WE'VE GOT A NEW FISH TANK?

26:10.525 --> 26:12.788
BUT WHERE ARE THE FISH?
-THERE ARE NO FISH.

26:13.789 --> 26:16.052
-YOU GOT A TURTLE?
-THERE ARE NO TURTLES.

26:16.183 --> 26:20.883
HOBIE, THIS IS
A SUB-OCEANIC CITY I DESIGNED
WHEN I WAS IN COLLEGE.

26:21.405 --> 26:24.844
TESTED AT 12 ATMOSPHERES.
-YOU BUILT THIS?

26:24.974 --> 26:26.410
-BUILT IT, DESIGNED IT,
EVERYTHING.

26:29.675 --> 26:32.025
-GRANDPA SURE MUST'VE
BEEN PROUD OF YOU.

26:32.155 --> 26:34.984
-YEAH, HE SAID IF I KEPT AT IT,
SOMEDAY I MIGHT BUILD
A REAL CITY ON THE OCEAN FLOOR.

26:35.768 --> 26:37.508
-WHY DIDN'T YOU?

26:38.161 --> 26:39.989
-BECAUSE I'D HAVE TO WORK
IN AN OFFICE FOR A FEW YEARS
IN ORDER TO DO IT.

26:40.599 --> 26:42.252
-BUT LOOK WHAT YOU'D HAVE BUILT
WHEN YOU WERE DONE.

26:42.383 --> 26:44.428
-YEAH.
-[KNOCK ON DOOR]

26:44.559 --> 26:46.300
-OH! GET THE DOOR.
THAT'S GRANDMA AND GRANDPA.
I'LL BE UPSTAIRS.

26:46.430 --> 26:47.649
-YEAH, SURE.

26:53.002 --> 26:55.614
HEY, GRANDMA!
-HI! HELLO, SWEETHEART.

26:55.744 --> 26:59.487
WHAT'S MY BOY BEEN UP TO TODAY?
-JUST TALKING WITH DAD.
LOOK WHAT HE BUILT.

26:59.618 --> 27:04.971
-OH, MY GOODNESS.
DO I REMEMBER THAT.
OH, LOOK AT IT.

27:21.770 --> 27:22.641
-MOM.

27:27.123 --> 27:28.777
-I TOLD HIM THAT YOU KNOW,

27:29.343 --> 27:31.911
AND THAT IT'S TIME
FOR THE TWO OF YOU
TO RESOLVE YOUR DIFFERENCES.

27:32.955 --> 27:35.001
I'LL BE WITH HOBIE IN HIS ROOM.

27:35.131 --> 27:38.265
I'LL, UH, TELL HIM
ABOUT HIS GRANDDAD
IF YOU WANT ME TO--

27:38.395 --> 27:39.701
-NO. NO, IT'S OKAY.

27:40.789 --> 27:42.835
I'LL TALK TO HOBIE
AFTER I TALK TO DAD.

27:45.446 --> 27:46.969
MOM, I DON'T KNOW
HOW TO TALK TO HIM.

27:47.883 --> 27:51.452
-COME FROM LOVE, MITCH.
COME FROM LOVE.

27:52.453 --> 27:53.410
-OKAY.

28:03.072 --> 28:05.248
[FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING]

28:08.904 --> 28:11.254
-I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU KEPT THIS.
-YEAH.

28:14.301 --> 28:16.607
YOU WANT A PEPSI?
-COFFEE IF YOU HAVE IT.

28:16.738 --> 28:19.393
-YEAH, NO PROBLEM.
-IF YOU HAVEN'T GOT ANY MADE,
IT'S ALL RIGHT.

28:19.523 --> 28:21.917
-NO, DAD, IT'S NO PROBLEM.
-YOU SURE?

28:22.048 --> 28:23.005
-ABSOLUTELY.

28:24.180 --> 28:26.792
-WOW, MITCH.
OH, YOU HAVE TALENT, MITCH.

28:26.922 --> 28:29.577
YOU HAVE...
REAL, GENUINE TALENT.

28:29.708 --> 28:31.927
-I HAD SOME TALENT, MAYBE.

28:32.667 --> 28:36.279
-A TALENT IS GOD-GIVEN.
IT'S THERE FROM BIRTH TO DEATH.

28:36.410 --> 28:38.847
IF YOU DON'T PUT IT TO USE,
YOU MIGHT AS WELL
NOT HAVE LIVED.

28:42.590 --> 28:43.591
-WELL...

28:44.548 --> 28:46.376
THERE'S ALL KINDS
OF TALENT, DAD.

28:47.943 --> 28:49.728
WHAT DO YOU SAY WE TAKE
A LITTLE WALK, YOU KNOW?

28:49.858 --> 28:51.512
GET SOME AIR WHILE
THE COFFEE'S BREWING?

28:51.642 --> 28:52.818
-SURE, GOOD IDEA.

29:11.314 --> 29:13.273
I BET YOU WANT TO BE
BURIED AT SEA, RIGHT?

29:15.057 --> 29:16.319
-PROBABLY.

29:17.233 --> 29:20.106
-I WANT TO BURIED
IN THE FOUNDATION
OF A BUILDING I DESIGNED.

29:20.236 --> 29:22.108
IN LIMESTONE
SO THAT MY BODY DISSOLVES,

29:22.238 --> 29:24.240
BECOMES PART
OF THE BUILDING ITSELF.

29:26.895 --> 29:27.940
INTERESTING, ISN'T IT?

29:29.332 --> 29:31.552
-WHAT?
-THE WAY PEOPLE
WANT TO BE BURIED.

29:31.682 --> 29:33.989
DO YOU SUPPOSE BASEBALL PLAYERS
WANT TO SPEND ETERNITY

29:34.120 --> 29:36.383
BURIED BENEATH THE POSITION
THEY PLAYED ALL THEIR CAREERS?

29:36.513 --> 29:38.515
-I DON'T WANT TO TALK ABOUT
WHERE PEOPLE WANT TO BE BURIED.

29:38.646 --> 29:40.953
-WHAT ELSE DO YOU WANT
TO TALK ABOUT?

29:41.083 --> 29:43.999
DEATH IS GOING TO BE
THE TOPIC OF CONVERSATION,
ISN'T IT? MINE IN PARTICULAR.

29:44.130 --> 29:46.480
-DAD--
-I'VE COME TO GRIPS
WITH IT, SON.

29:47.481 --> 29:49.265
-IT'S REALLY-- IT'S...

29:49.396 --> 29:51.354
IT'S NOT AS SCARY
AS I THOUGHT IT WOULD BE.

29:58.318 --> 30:00.842
-HOW LONG--
-OH, I DON'T KNOW.

30:00.973 --> 30:03.584
YOUR MOTHER DISCUSSED THAT
WITH THE DOCTOR. I DON'T WANT
TO HEAR TEN, NINE, EIGHT, SEVEN.

30:03.714 --> 30:06.761
-NO, NO, NO, NO.
HOW LONG BEFORE YOU RETIRE?

30:08.850 --> 30:09.895
-WHY DO YOU NEED TO KNOW?

30:10.939 --> 30:13.202
-WELL, I'VE BEEN
THINKING ABOUT IT, AND...

30:14.595 --> 30:17.424
MAYBE THERE'S TIME I EXPLORE
MY OTHER TALENTS, YOU KNOW?

30:17.554 --> 30:18.860
I MEAN, IF I HAVE THEM.

30:18.991 --> 30:21.123
-IT IS TIME,
AND YOU HAVE THEM, MITCH.

30:21.907 --> 30:24.083
LONG AFTER I'M GONE,
LONG AFTER YOU'RE GONE,

30:24.213 --> 30:28.435
OUR WORK WILL ENDURE IN GLASS
AND STONE AND STEEL
AND BRICK AND WOOD.

30:28.914 --> 30:31.830
IT'S A TANGIBLE LEGACY.
SOMETHING TO REALLY
LEAVE BEHIND, MITCH.

30:34.267 --> 30:36.835
-MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT, DAD.
MAYBE YOU'RE RIGHT.

30:50.587 --> 30:52.198
-REMEMBER WHEN YOU HAD
TO HOLD MY HAND

30:52.328 --> 30:54.156
JUST SO I COULD
JUMP OFF THE PIER?

30:54.287 --> 30:55.723
-DO YOU WANT ME
TO COME UP THERE WITH YOU?

30:56.637 --> 30:59.248
-NO, I LEARNED THAT
FACING YOUR FEAR ISN'T ENOUGH.

30:59.379 --> 31:00.815
YOU HAVE TO DEFEAT IT,

31:00.946 --> 31:03.513
AND I DEFEATED IT AND YOU
KAMIKAZE BIKING,

31:03.644 --> 31:05.864
SO JUST KEEP YOUR HANDS
TO YOURSELF, MATT BRODY.

32:05.967 --> 32:08.535
-YOU OKAY, SUMMER?
-JUST TAKE ME HOME, PLEASE.

32:31.427 --> 32:33.952
-HEY, YOU. HEY.

32:34.082 --> 32:36.215
COME ON HOME, BABY.
IT'S GETTING COLD.

32:37.303 --> 32:39.914
-MOM, WHAT AM I GONNA DO?
I MEAN...

32:40.045 --> 32:43.483
I'M A LIFEGUARD,
AND I'M SUDDENLY AFRAID
TO GO IN THE WATER.

32:43.613 --> 32:46.312
-OH... WELL, I DON'T KNOW,
BUT WHATEVER IT IS,

32:46.442 --> 32:48.270
I KNOW THAT YOU'RE
GONNA GET OVER IT.

32:48.792 --> 32:51.186
NOW, COME ON. IT'S COLD.

32:52.318 --> 32:54.233
HONEY, WHAT IS IT?
WHAT'S WRONG?

32:54.363 --> 32:57.801
-IT'S THAT COLOR.
THE WATER'S ALWAYS
THIS AWFUL COLOR GREEN.

33:00.630 --> 33:03.633
-OH, MY GOD.
-MOM, WHAT'S THE MATTER?

33:04.243 --> 33:07.942
-OH, THIS IS ALL MY FAULT.
-MOM, WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

33:08.073 --> 33:09.161
-OH, HONEY...

33:09.813 --> 33:11.685
YOU WERE SO LITTLE,
I NEVER THOUGHT...

33:12.555 --> 33:14.166
-MOM, WHAT ARE YOU
TALKING ABOUT?

33:15.210 --> 33:16.081
-SUMMER...

33:17.386 --> 33:19.606
SOMETHING HAPPENED TO YOU
WHEN YOU WERE REALLY LITTLE.

33:19.736 --> 33:22.087
YOU COULDN'T HAVE BEEN
MORE THAN FIVE. I JUST--

33:22.217 --> 33:23.392
-WHAT?

33:23.523 --> 33:24.872
-OH, HONEY, I...

33:26.526 --> 33:27.918
YOUR STEPFATHER.

33:28.919 --> 33:32.575
HE GOT MAD AT YOU BECAUSE
YOU WERE THROWING STONES
INTO A REDWOOD HOT TUB.

33:33.576 --> 33:35.056
SO, HE THREW YOU IN.

33:38.059 --> 33:39.669
AND HE PUT THE LID ON IT.

33:47.677 --> 33:49.897
THAT LID WAS TOO HEAVY
FOR YOU TO MOVE.

33:53.161 --> 33:56.121
HONEY, THE PUMP WAS ON.
THE HEAT WAS OFF,

33:56.817 --> 33:58.601
BUT THE WATER...

33:58.732 --> 34:00.560
IT WAS GREEN AND BUBBLY.

34:08.784 --> 34:11.484
I PUSHED THE TOP OFF,
I PULLED YOU OUT.

34:11.918 --> 34:15.270
HONEY, THAT NIGHT,
I TOOK YOU AND WE LEFT.

34:16.402 --> 34:18.143
-WHY DIDN'T I EVER
REMEMBER THIS?

34:18.795 --> 34:20.362
-I DON'T KNOW.

34:21.275 --> 34:23.670
I WAS JUST SO GRATEFUL
THAT YOU SEEMED TO FORGET IT.

34:24.931 --> 34:28.456
I NEVER REALIZED IT WOULD HAVE
THIS KIND OF EFFECT ON YOU.

34:29.284 --> 34:31.069
I'M SO SORRY.

34:33.114 --> 34:34.637
-IT'S NOT YOUR FAULT.

34:39.860 --> 34:42.167
THIS ALL STARTED
THE NIGHT IN THE CANALS.

34:43.210 --> 34:46.083
THOSE GREEN LIGHT STICKS
MUST HAVE TRIGGERED MY MEMORIES.

34:47.955 --> 34:49.478
-OH, BABY.

34:50.478 --> 34:51.828
MY GIRL.

34:55.179 --> 34:56.877
MY SWEET GIRL.

35:00.315 --> 35:03.536
-HEY, IT'S PAST MIDNIGHT.
-CATCH.

35:03.666 --> 35:06.408
-AREN'T YOU TIRED?
-NOT REALLY. ARE YOU?

35:07.931 --> 35:11.152
-NO. NO, NOT REALLY. UM...

35:11.283 --> 35:14.764
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU ANYWAY.
-YEAH?

35:16.331 --> 35:19.247
-HOBIE...
YOUR GRANDFATHER, UM...

35:19.378 --> 35:20.640
-DAD...

35:22.772 --> 35:24.513
GRANDMA TOLD ME ABOUT GRANDPA.

35:25.253 --> 35:28.300
SHE SAID YOU WANTED TO,
BUT I KNEW THERE WAS
SOMETHING WRONG,

35:28.430 --> 35:29.344
SO I ASKED HER.

35:30.389 --> 35:31.346
WELL, SHE TOLD ME.

35:34.044 --> 35:36.612
-DID SHE TELL YOU
THAT HE WANTS ME
TO TAKE OVER HIS BUSINESS?

35:38.092 --> 35:38.919
-YEAH.

35:40.355 --> 35:42.183
-THAT MEANS WE'LL HAVE
TO MOVE TO PHOENIX.

35:42.879 --> 35:44.316
-HOW DO YOU FEEL ABOUT THAT?

35:45.230 --> 35:46.753
-I WOULD MISS
MY FRIENDS AND ALL,

35:47.406 --> 35:48.972
BUT IF YOU WANTED TO,
I WOULD.

35:51.714 --> 35:55.849
DO YOU?
-NO. NO, I DON'T.

35:57.981 --> 35:59.418
BUT I THINK IT'S
THE RIGHT THING TO DO.

36:00.419 --> 36:01.898
-THEN MAYBE WE SHOULD.

36:02.029 --> 36:04.074
MAYBE I'LL BECOME
AN ARCHITECT TOO, SOMEDAY.

36:04.727 --> 36:06.686
-YOU'RE GONNA BE WHATEVER
YOU WANT TO BE.

36:07.817 --> 36:09.863
-DAD...
-YEAH?

36:10.472 --> 36:11.908
-I JUST WANT TO BE LIKE YOU.

36:13.606 --> 36:14.433
-COME HERE.

36:16.043 --> 36:20.178
-I LOVE YOU, DAD.
-I LOVE YOU TOO, PAL.

36:24.312 --> 36:26.401
-[MUSIC PLAYING ON RADIO]

36:37.847 --> 36:40.110
-HONEY, I'M HOT.
LET'S GO IN THE WATER.

36:40.241 --> 36:42.896
-WAIT, HONEY. YOU THINK
THAT'S SUCH A GOOD IDEA?

36:43.723 --> 36:46.639
-THE DOCTOR SAID IT'D BE FINE
UNTIL AT LEAST SIX MONTHS.

36:47.292 --> 36:49.468
COME ON.
-OKAY.

36:51.557 --> 36:52.688
THERE WE GO.

36:59.086 --> 37:00.130
-COME ON.

37:12.099 --> 37:14.580
-OH, HEY, SUMMER.
THESE ARE MY GRANDPARENTS.

37:14.710 --> 37:17.887
-HELLO, I'M IRENE BUCHANNON,
AND THIS IS MY HUSBAND, AL.

37:18.018 --> 37:19.672
-HOW DO YOU DO?
-HI, IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU.

37:19.802 --> 37:21.587
YOUR SON'S A GREAT GUY
TO WORK FOR.

37:21.717 --> 37:23.763
-HE'S A GREAT GUY PERIOD.

37:23.893 --> 37:25.678
-I WAS JUST ABOUT
TO GO TALK TO HIM.
DOES HE KNOW YOU'RE HERE?

37:25.808 --> 37:27.506
-NO. ACTUALLY, IT'S A SURPRISE.

37:27.636 --> 37:30.596
-WELL, YOU'D BETTER BE CAREFUL.
HE'S RIGHT THERE, ON TOWER 14.

37:30.726 --> 37:32.032
-THANK YOU.
-THANK YOU, DEAR.
LOVELY TO MEET YOU, TOO.

37:32.162 --> 37:33.338
-GOODBYE, SUMMER.
-GOODBYE.

37:34.774 --> 37:37.298
-THIS PLACE IS
AN ARCHITECTURAL NIGHTMARE.

37:37.429 --> 37:39.822
HOW COULD MITCH WORK HERE?

37:40.170 --> 37:41.781
-LOOK OUT THERE
AND YOU'LL SEE.

37:43.130 --> 37:45.872
-WHAT?
-THAT'S WHERE THE OCEAN IS.

37:53.880 --> 37:55.229
-HELP!

37:56.099 --> 38:00.278
-WOW! YOU GUYS, HURRY UP.
DAD'S GOING ON A RESCUE.

38:00.408 --> 38:03.498
WE CAN WATCH THROUGH THESE.
COME ON! RIGHT OVER THERE.

38:03.629 --> 38:05.021
SEE HIM?

38:06.022 --> 38:08.895
-WOMAN: HEY, LOOK!
-MAN: MAN, CHECK IT OUT.

38:09.678 --> 38:11.724
-LET ME TAKE A LOOK.

38:29.829 --> 38:32.658
-HOBIE, UH, MAY I, PLEASE?
-YEAH, SURE.

38:52.808 --> 38:54.549
-[SIRENS BLARING]

39:02.514 --> 39:03.906
-MAN: KIDS, GET OVER HERE.

39:29.671 --> 39:31.369
-[SIRENS BLARING]

39:31.499 --> 39:32.935
-MITCH: GOOD JOB.
-MATT: THANKS.

39:50.213 --> 39:53.391
-WHEN DAD WAS MY AGE,
WERE HE AND GRANDPA
REALLY CLOSE?

39:54.827 --> 39:57.177
-SOMETIMES, IT TAKES
AN ENTIRE LIFETIME

39:57.307 --> 39:59.701
TO GET CLOSE TO SOMEONE
YOU LOVE MOST.

40:03.357 --> 40:04.706
-THANKS A LOT.

40:15.717 --> 40:18.851
DAD, WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
YOU SHOULDN'T WALK
ALL THE WAY OUT HERE.

40:19.286 --> 40:21.419
-[OUT OF BREATH]
I NEED THE EXERCISE.

40:22.071 --> 40:23.116
OH!

40:25.510 --> 40:27.816
IS SHE GONNA BE ALL RIGHT?
THE ONE YOU RESCUED?

40:28.338 --> 40:30.515
-YEAH!
YEAH, SHE'S GONNA BE FINE.
IT WAS ONLY A CRAMP.

40:30.645 --> 40:32.734
THANK GOD.
SHE WAS PREGNANT.

40:34.519 --> 40:36.521
-SO, YOU ACTUALLY
SAVED TWO LIVES.

40:38.653 --> 40:39.872
OH, MITCH...

40:41.351 --> 40:42.657
I'M SORRY.
-NO, DAD, DON'T--

40:42.788 --> 40:44.964
-NO, LISTEN. NO, LISTEN.
NO, NO, NO, NO.

40:45.094 --> 40:47.357
BEFORE THIS, I NEVER
REALLY COMPREHENDED
WHAT IT IS YOU DO DOWN HERE.

40:47.488 --> 40:50.404
I'VE BEEN TALKING TO YOU ABOUT
LEAVING BUILDINGS AS A LEGACY,

40:51.100 --> 40:52.537
AND YOU'RE LEAVING LIVES.

40:53.842 --> 40:56.323
THAT WOMAN CAN NOW
GIVE BIRTH TO A CHILD

40:57.150 --> 40:59.718
THAT MIGHT NOT
HAVE EVER BEEN BORN
IF IT WEREN'T FOR YOU.

41:00.980 --> 41:04.418
THAT'S THE GREATEST LEGACY
ANY MAN CAN LEAVE.

41:06.202 --> 41:08.030
-IT'S YOUR LEGACY, TOO.

41:09.205 --> 41:12.078
I'M YOUR CHILD.
-OH, MITCH...

41:15.385 --> 41:18.519
LISTEN, YOU TAKE CARE OF HOBIE.
YOU MAKE SURE HE DOES
WHATEVER MAKES HIM HAPPY.

41:18.650 --> 41:20.390
-OKAY.
-ALL RIGHT?

41:21.087 --> 41:23.132
-HE WANTS TO BE AN ARCHITECT.
-REALLY?

41:23.263 --> 41:24.525
-YEAH.
-DOES HE HAVE TALENT?

41:24.656 --> 41:26.092
-I DON'T KNOW.
-WELL, LET'S GO FIND OUT.

41:26.222 --> 41:28.224
-WAIT, WAIT. DAD, THIS IS...

41:28.355 --> 41:29.835
THIS IS MY OFFICE.
I CAN'T LEAVE--

41:29.965 --> 41:31.532
-OH, YEAH.
REALLY, WHY, OF COURSE.

41:31.663 --> 41:33.969
I KNOW. YOU STAY HERE.
I'VE GOT A PROJECT FOR HOBIE.

41:34.100 --> 41:35.928
I'LL HAVE HIM REDESIGN
THAT DREADFUL THING.

41:36.494 --> 41:37.538
-WHAT?

41:38.191 --> 41:40.323
-IF YOU'RE GONNA
KEEP WORKING HERE,

41:40.454 --> 41:42.282
YOU'VE GOT TO HAVE
AT LEAST A DECENTLY DESIGNED
HEADQUARTERS BUILDING.

41:42.412 --> 41:44.893
THAT THING HAS
NO FUNCTIONAL FLOOR OR ANYTHING.

42:05.261 --> 42:07.916
[ENDING SONG PLAYING]
